==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ligeance
<hw>Li"geance</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧"j⟦ait⟧ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>ligeance</ets>, <ets>ligance</ets>. See <er>Liege</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The connection between sovereign and
subject by which they were mutually bound, the former to protection and
the securing of justice, the latter to faithful service;
allegiance.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>ligeancy</asp> and
<asp>liegance</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligement</ent>⟦br⟧
